{{POV|date=October 2014}}

'''Churn and burn''' refers to a tactic used by [[Wal-Mart|large anti-union businesses]] with high turnover in order to bust an already-existent [[labour union|union]] in a given workplace.  "Churning" refers to the management practice of filtering new workers based on their support of unionism.  In a large business with poorly paid, entry-level workers with a high rate of turnover, support for a union can be gradually reduced by making sure during the hiring process that only [[union busting|anti-union workers]] are hired.  Eventually, support drops low enough to "burn" the union through [[NLRB election procedures#Decertification_elections|decertification]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Chung|first=Andrew|title=Wal-Mart workers hope to show their union the door|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/article/950705--wal-mart-workers-hope-to-show-their-union-the-door|newspaper=Toronto Star|date=March 8, 2011}}</ref> 

