'''Ivan Pilný''' (born July 6, 1944) is a Czech politician and former [[Microsoft]] executive who briefly served as [[Finance Minister of the Czech Republic]] from 24 May 2017 to 13 December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.eu/article/czech-president-fires-finance-minister-ending-political-crisis/ |title=Czech president fires finance minister, ending political crisis |publisher=[[POLITICO]]|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> From 2013 to 2017 Pilný was a member of the [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] (MP).

